entries.femaleVariant: [Sit] Hurry up and wait.
Hurry up and wait, then.
You're acting spooked, as if you're the first person ever to stand up to Saul.
Oh, save your breath, I don't need to be consoled.
Grr, was it someone I know?
Knew. Scorpion.
He came home from the war, head full of new ideas and a host of new contacts…
He tried to get Saul to lead us in joining Snake Nation. It would make us stronger, he said.
[Sit] Worried about Saul?
You worried about Saul?
I don't think he peeped a word of it to me. What did Saul do?
Saul dressed the guy down head to toe for messing with the family. Hell, he didn't send him on any jobs for a year.
Gee, really consoling, thanks.
You said yourself you didn't need any.
[Drink] Let's drink. To Scorpion.
Snake Nation? Saul was right.
Don't talk about the war much.
Think I'll try and get some shut-eye.
Oughta raise a glass to Scorpion.
Saul was right about Snake Nation.
Don't talk about the war much.
Gonna try and get some sleep.
OK. It'll be quite some time before the convoy comes through.
To Scorpion.
What's there to say? They just packed you into a panzer down in Mexico and said full speed ahead, soldier.
Then it was weeks talking either to yourself or the onboard AI, drinking iodide like water because your Geiger wouldn't shut up.
Mmhmm. I'm sprouting a rash on my ass just thinking about sitting in that boiling hot coffin.
Uh-huh. But you all can't wait to pack your asses into the Basilisk, huh?
That's different.
Completely different. You'll see once you're on board.
You should remain independent. Otherwise, could end up like…
entries.maleVariant: You should remain independent. Otherwise, you could end up like…

entries.femaleVariant: Like the Bakkers?
Mhm.
We'll manage just fine on our own. All we need is a few good jobs.
And that's why we're here today.
Scorpion would be proud.
To get people talking about the Aldecaldos again.
And to Jackie.
[Scooch closer] Gotten kinda cold.
Grown kinda cold out here.
Can tell you won't be getting any sleep.
Mad at me?
Wake me up if anything happens.
Couldn't sleep if you tried, could you?
Mad at me for somethin'?
entries.maleVariant: You mad at me for somethin'?

entries.femaleVariant: I'll just lie here a while, by your side, gazing at the stars.
Anything happens, wake me up. Unless you wanna nap, too.
Not true. But this is nice.
Catch some shut-eye with me?
That another area of your expertise? Got maps of the heavens in your library, too?
Of course. That's the Big Dipper. And do you see the small flickering star to the right?
Goodnight, V.
What? No, come on.
Not gonna nap?
You do? Oh dear, that means Ursa Major leak!
Yeeaah...?
[Drink]
The stars have emerged. We've but a few hours till dawn.
We've quite some time left till dusk.
Hm, the car could use another once-over.
V? Did you just doze off?
